On c. [[12 April]] [[1970]], [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] wrote '''[[Letters not published in "The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien"|a letter]] to [[Tom Shippey]]'''. Shippey received the letter on [[13 April]] [[1970]].<ref name=C>{{CG|C}}, p. 749</ref><ref name=Guide>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://www.tolkienguide.com/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?topic_id=1701&forum=17&post_id=9016#forumpost9016|articlename=Tolkien's letter to Shippey, April 1970|dated=|website=Guide|accessed=31 December 2011}}</ref>

*'''Subject:''' Comments on Shippey's paper "The Author as Philologist" (sent by Shippey to Tolkien).<ref name=C/>
*'''Publication:''' Quotes from the letter were published in ''[[The Road to Middle-earth]]''.<ref>[[Tom Shippey]], "Preface to the Second Edition", in ''The Road to Middle-earth''</ref> Shippey also briefly describes the letter in "Long Evolution: ''The History of Middle-earth'' and Its Merits" (in [[Arda (annual)|''Arda'']] 1987, Vol. VII, p.&nbsp;29)<ref name=Guide/> and in ''[[Roots and Branches]]''.<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://www.lotrplaza.com/forum/forum_posts.asp?TID=222668|articlename=Birmingham, Beorn, and elfland (posts from 06/Oct/2007 at 8:50pm and 07/Oct/2007 at 12:25am)|dated=|website=[http://www.lotrplaza.com/forum/default.asp?C=1&title=middleearth-related Lord of the Rings Fanatics Plaza Forums]|accessed=31 December 2011}}</ref>

